# ZDU test override env — disables policy + REST authorization so the
# test framework's REST writes via personal access token are not blocked
# by the new master HEAD validators (PrivilegeConstraintsValidator, etc.).
# The ZDU test signal is aspect migration, not authorization; bypassing
# both layers removes that interference.
#
# Used only when DATAHUB_LOCAL_COMMON_ENV=zdu-test.env is set in the
# calling shell (Compose YAML expands ${DATAHUB_LOCAL_COMMON_ENV:-empty.env}).
AUTH_POLICIES_ENABLED=false
REST_API_AUTHORIZATION_ENABLED=false
# Disable bearer-token authentication entirely. After the nuke wipes
# MySQL, the existing PERSONAL token in ~/.datahubenv has no stateful
# record and is rejected; regenerating via `datahub init` also fails
# because master HEAD's canGeneratePersonalAccessToken returns false
# under AUTH_POLICIES_ENABLED=false. With METADATA_SERVICE_AUTH_ENABLED
# off, the framework's REST calls don't need a token at all — fits the
# ZDU test signal (aspect migration + reindex), not auth.
METADATA_SERVICE_AUTH_ENABLED=false
# G20a NOTE: ELASTICSEARCH_BUILD_INDICES_INCREMENTAL_REINDEX_ENABLED is
# NOT set here. It must NOT propagate to the initial system-update run
# at stack startup (that run is responsible for CREATING all ES indices
# via the legacy BuildIndicesPre/Step/Post path; the incremental path
# only reindexes EXISTING indices and would leave fresh ES empty,
# crashing GMS at boot on lifecyclestagetypeindex_v2 not_found).
# Instead, the flag is passed only via env_overrides on Phase 4 / Phase 8
# explicit `docker compose run system-update-debug -u SystemUpdateBlocking`
# invocations — see upgrade_blocking.py and upgrade_nonblocking.py.
#
# G20d — enable rollback dual-write so UpdateIndicesUpgradeStrategy is
# instantiated. The bean is gated by @ConditionalOnProperty on
# elasticsearch.buildIndices.rollbackDualWriteEnabled; without this flag
# Spring doesn't load the strategy at all → no "Recorded dual-write start
# time …" log line ever fires → dual_write_start_times stays {} no matter
# which service we tail → catch_up_windows stays {} → TC-301/303/304 have
# nothing to validate. The application.yaml fallback chain is
#   ${ELASTICSEARCH_BUILD_INDICES_ROLLBACK_DUAL_WRITE_ENABLED:${ZDU_STAGE_20:false}}
# so this env var is the canonical override path.
ELASTICSEARCH_BUILD_INDICES_ROLLBACK_DUAL_WRITE_ENABLED=true